# HexaBill UI/UX Design System

When editing any file under `frontend/hexabill-ui`, **always** align with the project design lock and master prompt.

## Must read (or recall)

- **Full design system & page fixes:** `docs/HEXABILL_UX_UI_MASTER_PROMPT.md`
- **Lock & quick reference:** `docs/UI_UX_DESIGN_LOCK.md`

## Non-negotiable rules

1. **Mobile-first, zero horizontal scroll** — `overflow-x: hidden`, `max-width: 100%`; tables become cards on &lt; 768px.
2. **8px grid** — Mobile: p-4, gap-4; Desktop: p-6, gap-6. No random p-1/p-2 or p-8+.
3. **Icons** — **Lucide only** (from `lucide-react`). Remove all emojis and other icon sets.
4. **Colors** — Neutrals (neutral-50…900) for most UI; primary-500/600 only for main actions; no gradients or colored shadows.
5. **Cards** — `bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl`; **no shadow** except dropdowns (shadow-md) and modals (shadow-lg).
6. **Typography** — Min 12px; use the scale in the master prompt (e.g. text-sm 14px mobile, text-base 16px body).

Before finishing UI work, run the validation checklist in the master prompt (mobile/tablet/desktop + visual).

Design inspiration: Linear, Notion, YouTube Analytics, Stripe. **Not** Material, Bootstrap defaults, or generic AI-style templates.
